Subject: Re: [VB] Rubberized Coatings - an Interior Rust Preventative?

> I used a non-petroleum based Henry roof patch goop on the inside of my '63 DC.
> Uses some kind of clay as the binder and is water soluble until it dries. No
> solvent smell and it doesn't melt in the 110f heat we have here. Leaking gas
> has washed some of it off the interior near the filler though. Can't verify
> the rust repelling ability, but it keeps condensed moisture off the inside of
> the body and soaks up road and wind noise pretty good.

I believe I used the same stuff to seal my windshield bottom frames before I
put the glass/gaskets in. Worked really well, except for the disaster when I
opened the can & it sprayed all over the back flap of a new canopy I had
treated -had to use the canvas on my own truck after that.

